gobblin.configuration

Class State

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.configuration.State

    public class State
extends Object
implements Writable
    A serializable wrapper class that can be persisted for Properties.

      • appendToListProp

        public void appendToListProp(String key,
                             String value)
        Appends the input value to a list property that can be retrieved with getPropAsList(java.lang.String).

        List properties are internally stored as comma separated strings. Adding a value that contains commas (for example "a,b,c") will essentially add multiple values to the property ("a", "b", and "c"). This is similar to the way that Configuration works.

        Parameters:
        key - property key
        value - property value (if it includes commas, it will be split by the commas).

      • appendToSetProp

        public void appendToSetProp(String key,
                            String value)
        Appends the input value to a set property that can be retrieved with getPropAsSet(java.lang.String).

        Set properties are internally stored as comma separated strings. Adding a value that contains commas (for example "a,b,c") will essentially add multiple values to the property ("a", "b", and "c"). This is similar to the way that Configuration works.

        Parameters:
        key - property key
        value - property value (if it includes commas, it will be split by the commas).
